00.Summary:
Import micro-CT data (Section 2.2) of the extracted section from the tensile test specimen.


Micro-CT images were captured with a ZEISS Xradia Versa x-ray machine and imported with the ITK::Import Images filter.

03.Summary:
This section creates a mask of the part boundary and isolates the density of the part volume (Section 3.1).


Gradient Magnitude highlights the gradient in the part

Robust Automatic Threshold creates a boolean array (mask) of the part

Isolate larget feature fills holes in the boolean mask of the part

12.Summary: General alignment with the CAD target performed with Rotate Sample Reference Frame and Set Origin and Spacing.

15.Summary:
This section classifies anomalies within the micro-CT data using Otsu's method (Section 4.0).


Grayscale fillhole removes local minima

Attribute array calculator subtracts the density array from the fillhole array leaving only the local minima

Otsu Multiple Thresholds filter segregates the local minima into a seperate class

20.Summary: This section creates a point cloud of the part boundary to use for registration (Section 3.1).

27.Filter_Human_Label: Extract Internal Surfaces from Triangle Geometry

33.Summary:
This section performs registration using ICP to align the micro-CT dataset to the CAD file (Section 3.1).


Iterative closest point computes a transformation matrix using the surface point clouds of both parts

Apply transformation to geometry peforms the transformation on the CT image array
